A group of Niger Delta contractors with the Presidential Amnesty programme has stormed the office of the coordinator of the Amnesty Programme  demanding payment for contracts they had executed under the programme. This is even as President Muhammadu Buhari approved the appointment of Col. Milland Dixion Dikio (rtd) as interim administrator  of the Amnesty Programme. The leader of the group, Mr. Michael Kelikume who led the group on protest yesterday in Abuja, disclosed that contractors had not been paid for work done for over three to four years. He said that the bank loans they obtained to execute the various contracts had accumulated, thereby causing them problems. According to Kelikume, “We delivered jobs successively for the amnesty office as far back as three to four years ago and we  have not been paid our money. “These are jobs that had been done long ago, these payments are long overdue, we have borrowed money from bank, from other financial institutions and friends, what we are demanding for is that the payment be made immediately,” he said.